    {
      "id": "sprint_1776847582318_2",
      "name": "Sprint 2: Managed Agent Core Loop & CLI Interface",
      "description": "Implement the bare-bones managed agent following the quickstart docs — wire up a single agent invocation with one example tool, run the agent loop end-to-end, and expose it through a simple CLI that accepts a user prompt and prints the agent response.",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "individualTasks": [
        {
          "id": "860e7092-676c-48c9-93a3-eda835dab10c",
          "title": "Implement tool dispatcher for agent tool_use blocks",
          "description": "Create `src/agent/toolDispatcher.ts` exporting a `dispatchTool(name, input)` function that looks up the handler in `src/data/toolHandlers.ts` and invokes it with the provided input, returning a string result. Handle the happy path only — assume the tool name exists in the handler map. This bridges the agent loop's `tool_use` content blocks to the Sprint 1 mock handlers.",
          "purpose": "Provides the execution layer that converts Anthropic SDK tool_use requests into concrete handler invocations during the agent loop.",
          "functionality": "Routes a tool name and input object to the matching handler and returns its stringified result for inclusion in a tool_result message.",
          "successCriteria": [
            "`dispatchTool` returns the mock result string for the sample tool defined in Sprint 1",
            "Function accepts `(name: string, input: Record<string, unknown>)` and returns `string`",
            "Module imports handlers from `src/data/toolHandlers.ts`"
          ],
          "status": "completed",
          "priority": "high",
          "relevantFiles": [
            {
              "path": "src/agent/toolDispatcher.ts",
              "action": "create"
            },
            {
              "path": "src/data/toolHandlers.ts",
              "action": "read"
            },
            {
              "path": "src/data/tools.ts",
              "action": "read"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "e515c36d-af99-466d-a68a-77af2a07d2d8",
          "title": "Implement managed agent loop with Anthropic Messages API",
          "description": "Create `src/agent/runAgent.ts` exporting `runAgent(userPrompt: string): Promise<string>`. Instantiate a `ConversationState`, seed it with the user prompt, then enter a while loop that calls `client.messages.create` with the system prompt, `TOOLS`, and current messages. On `stop_reason === 'tool_use'`, dispatch each tool_use block via the dispatcher and append tool_result messages; on `stop_reason === 'end_turn'`, concatenate text blocks and return. Use model `claude-sonnet-4-5` with `max_tokens: 1024`.",
          "purpose": "Implements the core quickstart agent loop that ties together the SDK client, tool definitions, handlers, and conversation state into a complete multi-turn tool-using agent.",
          "functionality": "Runs a managed agent end-to-end: sends messages, handles tool_use by invoking handlers, loops until `end_turn`, and returns the final assistant text.",
          "successCriteria": [
            "`runAgent` returns a string containing the final assistant text response",
            "Loop invokes `dispatchTool` for every `tool_use` block returned by the API",
            "Loop terminates cleanly when the API returns `stop_reason: 'end_turn'`",
            "Tool results are appended to conversation state with matching `tool_use_id`",
            "Uses `SYSTEM_PROMPT` and `TOOLS` imported from the `src/data` modules"
          ],
          "status": "completed",
          "priority": "critical",
          "relevantFiles": [
            {
              "path": "src/agent/runAgent.ts",
              "action": "create"
            },
            {
              "path": "src/config/anthropic.ts",
              "action": "read"
            },
