        {
          "id": "8f259a2a-6f02-4b89-b47a-907860446a8a",
          "title": "Add verbose turn-by-turn logging to the agent loop",
          "description": "Modify `src/agent/runAgent.ts` to log each iteration: print a header for every API call, log any `tool_use` blocks (name + input) before dispatch, and log the returned tool result. Keep output readable with clear section separators. This is the primary way to observe the managed agent behavior in the POC demo.",
          "purpose": "Makes the quickstart agent loop observable from the CLI so viewers can see tool calls and results rather than only the final answer.",
          "functionality": "Prints a trace of each agent turn — request boundary, tool_use blocks, tool_result content — to stdout during `runAgent` execution.",
