    {
      "id": "sprint_1776859449619_j3167b634",
      "name": "Sprint 6: Database & API Foundation",
      "description": "Set up a SQLite database with the full workflow schema (workflows, workflow_runs, run_steps, run_events, approvals), wire up REST API endpoints for workflow and run management, and implement a JSON schema validator that enforces node/edge rules before execution.",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "individualTasks": [
        {
          "id": "task_1776859449667_0_jkf5l",
          "title": "Install and configure SQLite with Prisma",
          "description": "Install prisma, @prisma/client, and sqlite3. Initialize Prisma with SQLite datasource. Create schema.prisma with models for: Workflow (id, name, schema JSON, version, createdAt), WorkflowRun (id, workflowId, status enum pending/running/completed/failed, inputJson, createdAt, completedAt), RunStep (id, runId, nodeId, status, inputJson, outputJson, agentSessionId, startedAt, completedAt), RunEvent (id, runId, stepId, eventType, payload JSON, createdAt), Approval (id, stepId, slackChannel, slackUserId, decision, comment, createdAt). Run prisma migrate dev to generate the DB and client.",
          "status": "completed",
          "priority": "critical"
        },
        {
          "id": "task_1776859449667_1_86iyh",
          "title": "Build /workflows REST endpoints",
          "description": "Create src/api/workflowRoutes.ts with Express Router. Implement: POST /workflows — accept { name, schema } body, validate schema (see next task), persist to DB, return { id, name, version }. GET /workflows — list all workflows (id, name, version, createdAt). GET /workflows/:id — return full workflow including schema JSON. Mount the router in src/server.ts at /api.",
          "status": "completed",
          "priority": "critical"
        },
        {
          "id": "task_1776859449667_2_kkh8e",
          "title": "Build /runs REST endpoints",
          "description": "Create src/api/runRoutes.ts. Implement: POST /runs — accept { workflowId, input } body, create a WorkflowRun with status=pending, enqueue execution (call executeWorkflow in background, do not await), return { runId, status }. GET /runs — list recent runs (id, workflowId, status, createdAt). GET /runs/:id — return run detail including all RunSteps and RunEvents ordered by time. Mount at /api.",
          "status": "completed",
          "priority": "critical"
        },
        {
          "id": "task_1776859449667_3_cqvex",
