        {
          "id": "task_1776859502633_0_y2ahl",
          "title": "Implement the core executeWorkflow function",
          "description": "Create src/workflow/executor.ts exporting async function executeWorkflow(runId: string, workflowSchema: WorkflowSchema, input: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void>. Build a context object: { run: { id: runId, input }, steps: {} }. Start with entryNodeId. Loop: find the current node, execute it based on type, store outputs into context.steps[nodeId].outputs, find the next node using findNextEdge(edges, currentNodeId, context), repeat until a finalize node is reached or no next edge exists. On any error, update the run status to 'failed' and log a run_event with event_type='error'. Update run status to 'running' at start and 'completed' at end.",
          "status": "completed",
          "priority": "critical"
        },
        {
          "id": "task_1776859502633_1_opwhq",
          "title": "Implement agent node execution with Claude Managed Agents",
          "description": "Create src/workflow/nodeHandlers/agentNodeHandler.ts. For a node of type 'agent': resolve inputMapping values from context using JSONPath-like expressions ($.run.input.field and $.steps.nodeId.outputs.field). Create a new Anthropic client session per invocation (one session per step, per the spec's gotcha). Call anthropic.messages.create with model from node.modelConfig (default claude-opus-4-7), betas: ['interleaved-thinking-2025-05-14'] if effort is xhigh/max, system prompt from node.config.instructions (with {{variable}} template substitution from resolved inputs), max_tokens: 4096. Parse the text response as the agent output. Store agentSessionId on the RunStep record. Honor node.config.timeoutSeconds with a Promise.race timeout.",
          "status": "completed",
          "priority": "critical"
        },
        {
          "id": "task_1776859502633_2_ru7na",
          "title": "Implement input and finalize node handlers",
          "description": "Create src/workflow/nodeHandlers/inputNodeHandler.ts: validate that all requiredFields are present in the run input; if any are missing, throw a descriptive error. Return the input fields as outputs so they're available in context. Create src/workflow/nodeHandlers/finalizeNodeHandler.ts: mark the run as completed, write a run_event with event_type='workflow_completed' and payload containing summary of all step outputs. Both handlers should be simple — no external API calls.",
          "status": "completed",
          "priority": "high"
