          "title": "Fix: Re-saving a workflow fails with 409 Conflict",
          "description": "After the first save, WorkflowToolbar stores the returned workflow ID in state (line 69: setWorkflowId(result.id)). On subsequent saves, this ID is passed to serializeWorkflow (line 65: id: workflowId) and included in the POST /api/workflows body. The server extracts this ID (workflowRoutes.ts line 67-68) and calls createWorkflow() which does a Prisma create — hitting a unique constraint violation, returning 409. There is no PUT/PATCH update endpoint on the server. The user sees 'Workflow with this ID already exists' error toast every time they edit and re-save.\n\nFile: client/src/workflow/WorkflowToolbar.tsx",
          "status": "completed",
          "priority": "high",
