          "title": "Fix: MCP getRunStatus reads wrong event field names from server response",
          "description": "The MCP HTTP client (mcp/src/client.ts lines 126-131) defines RunDetail.events with fields 'type' and 'payload_json', but the server's GET /api/runs/:id endpoint returns events with fields 'event_type' and 'payload' (from persistence.ts toRunEventRow). In getRunStatus.ts (lines 27-33), the tool reads evt.payload_json (undefined) and evt.type (undefined), causing every event to render as '[undefined] ' instead of showing actual event types and payloads. The web client (client/src/types.ts RunEvent) correctly uses 'event_type' and 'payload', so only the MCP tool is affected.\n\nFile: mcp/src/client.ts",
          "status": "completed",
          "priority": "high",
