      "title": "[BUG-002] Navigate from editor to runs history page not working",
      "description": "Verify the React Router setup allows navigation to the /runs route and the run list page renders.\n\nExpected: After navigating to /runs, the URL pathname is /runs and the page mounts without falling back to a 404.\n\nActual: Expected window.location.pathname to contain \"/runs\", got \"/\"\n\nFailed at: Step 5: assert - Verify we are on the runs route\n\nPage: https://managed-agents-poc.onrender.com/\n\nConsole errors:\n• Expected window.location.pathname to contain \"/runs\", got \"/\"\n\nSteps:\n1. Start at the editor\n2. Allow editor to mount\n3. Navigate to the runs history page\n4. Allow runs page to mount\n5. Verify we are on the runs route\n6. Verify React app root is still mounted (route was matched)",
