      "title": "[BUG-003] Unknown route does not crash the app not working",
      "description": "Verify visiting an unmatched client-side route keeps the React app mounted (no white screen / crash).\n\nExpected: The React root remains mounted at an unknown path; the app does not throw an unrecoverable error.\n\nActual: Expected window.location.pathname to contain \"/this-route-does-not-exist\", got \"/\"\n\nFailed at: Step 4: assert - Verify URL reflects the attempted path\n\nPage: https://managed-agents-poc.onrender.com/\n\nConsole errors:\n• Expected window.location.pathname to contain \"/this-route-does-not-exist\", got \"/\"\n\nSteps:\n1. Navigate to a nonexistent client route\n2. Allow router to settle\n3. Verify the React root element is still mounted\n4. Verify URL reflects the attempted path",
